Agreed that the movie was a total bust, but his performance was good. To name a few, David Ehrlich, Mick LaSalle, Mark Kermode, David Rooney and more junior critics Simran hans, Max gao (all significant and metacritic profiled critics) have praised his performance. I could find only three reviews at metacritic that criticized his attempt at physical comedy. This review was written here citing that his performance received mixed reviews, so how come only three reviews sum up mixed reception?

Such career statements seem legitimate when an actor has reached a certain phase when he has done many projects among which many identifies as the defined character and has received acclaim for them, but Dornan's filmography is still expanding, and he has lately received (and maybe before The disastrous Shades) significant acclaim, so looking at articles of Judi Dench or Kate Winslet or other notable actors, it seems appropriate if it is put up later.
